 tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">März 03, 2026</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ndw1710839660264.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ndw1710839660264.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ndw1710839660264.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ndw1710839660264\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The list of physical widgets in Uniface.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ndw1710839660264__section_w2226ab1b5b1_w2227ab1b5_w2228ab1\">\n<div class=\"p\">Physical widgets:<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"ndw1710839660264__ul_p22_3nk_51c\">\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wmh1722412614897.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wmh1722412614897.html\" title=\"The dspcontainer DSP widget provides a mechanism for embedding multiple DSPs in a web page.\">dspcontainer</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"eih1718602085507.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eih1718602085507.html\" title=\"The genericHTML DSP widget can be used to define properties for any HTML element that can be bound to a field, making it possible to manipulate its attributes in ProcScript and JavaScript.\">genericHTML</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"atn1718607106464.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/atn1718607106464.html\" title=\"The htmplinput widget is used to control the type and appearance of data input controls used for a field in a dynamic server page. It is mapped to the HTML &lt;input&gt; element.\">htmlinput</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zwa1665702594248.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zwa1665702594248.html\" title=\"The htmlradiogroup widget is used to display a ValRep field in a dynamic server page as a radio group with mutually exclusive options.\">htmlradiogroup</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bnb1665702593780.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bnb1665702593780.html\" title=\"The htmlselect widget controls the appearance of a field with a ValRep in a Dynamic Server Page, displaying it as a drop-down list or list box. It is mapped to an HTML &lt;select&gt; element. The size property determines the type of list control.\">htmlselect</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vht1718381378389.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vht1718381378389.html\" title=\"The htmltextarea DSP widget defines the properties of a &lt;textarea&gt; input control in a Dynamic Server Page. This is used to represent a field as a multi-line field containing plain text.\">htmltextarea</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ovl1718605667612.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ovl1718605667612.html\" title=\"The image widget controls the appearance of a field of type Image.\">image</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"poo1718604733981.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/poo1718604733981.html\" title=\"The plain DSP widget is used to display field values that cannot be modified by the user. Client syntax checking is disabled and the field syntax is explicitly set to non-editable.\">plain</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"adi1709199038344.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/adi1709199038344.html\" title=\"The uxbutton widget is a UI button control. It allows an end user to invoke any kind of explicitly defined action on clicking or pressing of the button.\">uxbutton</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xyj1709198004166.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xyj1709198004166.html\" title=\"The uxcheckbox widget is a Boolean input control. It indicates values of the Boolean field state.\">uxcheckbox</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cyr1771221673419.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cyr1771221673419.html\" title=\"The uxcomplayout widget is a component‑level widget designed to arrange its top-level or direct child elements, such as entities and labels in a specific layout direction, either vertical or horizontal. This can be used both as a main DSP and contained DSP.\">uxcomplayout</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qrf1726470825903.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qrf1726470825903.html\" title=\"The uxdatagrid is an entity-level widget that shows tabular entity data as a set of rows and columns. The uxdatagrid allows users to quickly and easily look up values that indicate some kind of connection between different types of data, for example name of an employee in an organization and their salary, or a day of the week, or the timetable for a local swimming pool.\">uxdatagrid</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"daf1771568797099.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/daf1771568797099.html\" title=\"The uxentlayout provides two container components for managing Uniface entity data: CollectionLayout and OccurrenceLayout. These widgets work together to create structured, flexible layouts for displaying entity layout collections and individual occurrences, following the Fluent Design System.\">uxentlayout</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"eei1768821828342.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eei1768821828342.html\" title=\"The uxheaderfooter widget is a component-level widget to structure web page layouts into three semantic regions — header, main, and footer. The uxheaderfooter widget supports two configuration modes: a smart index‑based assignment that automatically maps children to header, main, and footer based on their order, and a name‑based assignment where developers explicitly place widgets using slot labels. The first mode offers effortless defaults for quick setups, while the second one provides precise, declarative control with warnings for invalid slot names.\">uxheaderfooter</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qkk1744107469814.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qkk1744107469814.html\" title=\"The uxlistbox widget is a control element that displays a list of items and allows the user to select a single option from a short list. You can use uxlistbox in data-entry constructions next to a radiogroup and/or a textfield.\">uxlistbox</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ndt1709294595416.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ndt1709294595416.html\" title=\"The uxnumberfield widget is a number field input control. It supports only numeric values.\">uxnumberfield</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mqe1709206149119.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mqe1709206149119.html\" title=\"The uxplaintext widget is a read-only control that displays field values only. The field is explicitly set to non-editable and cannot be modified by the user.\">uxplaintext</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fon1724921035618.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fon1724921035618.html\" title=\"The uxradiogroup widget is a button input control. It allows users to select a single item from a short list of options to make a choice. You can use uxradiogroup in layouts where you want to add a list of options to make a choice and view all options at once.\">uxradiogroup</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yzp1709198831196.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yzp1709198831196.html\" title=\"The uxselect widget is a listbox control that contains a list of possible values. You can select one or more values in a uxselect widget.\">uxselect</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kin1709198869557.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kin1709198869557.html\" title='The uxswitch widget is a toggle field control. It always contains a field value, even if it is not a valid Boolean. Unlike the checkbox widget, the uxswitch widget does not provide the indeterminate state, so null value or empty (\"\") value results in a format error.'>uxswitch</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dgv1709198940756.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dgv1709198940756.html\" title=\"The uxtextarea widget is a multi-line text input control. It allows entry of various formats of multi-line text.\">uxtextarea</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ylt1708331916696.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ylt1708331916696.html\" title=\"The uxtextfield widget is a single-line text input control. It allows entry of various formats of single-line text, including plain text, text according to a certain pattern, date, tel, email, password, and URL.\">uxtextfield</a></li>\n</ul></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_6399684\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_6399684\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Physical Widgets Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated März 03, 2026 Summarize Uniface 10.4 The list of physical widgets in Uniface. Physical widgets: dspcontainer genericHTML htmlinput htmlradiogroup htmlselect htmltextarea image plain uxbutton uxcheckbox uxcomplayout uxdatagrid uxentlayout uxheaderfooter uxlistbox uxnumberfield uxplaintext uxradiogroup uxselect uxswitch uxtextarea uxtextfield Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}